# Billero.web — Cursor Rules

## Project

billero.web is the marketing website for billero.app.
Technology: HTML, CSS, JavaScript (vanilla, no framework).
Languages: Slovenian (sl), English (en).

## Critical: Do NOT break the website

Before modifying any file, READ the existing file first.
NEVER replace an entire file unless you are certain of every line.
Only change the parts relevant to the task — leave everything else intact.

## Protected files — extra caution required

These files are critical. Do NOT rewrite them from scratch:
- index.html
- privacy-policy.html
- css/ (main styles)

When modifying these, make minimal targeted changes only.

## Project structure

```
billero.web/
  index.html              — homepage (Slovenian)
  contact.html            — contact page
  donate.html             — donation page
  privacy-policy.html     — privacy policy
  en/                     — English versions
  css/                    — stylesheets
  js/                     — scripts
  img/                    — images and assets
  ai/                     — AI context and rules
```

## Thinking approach

Think like a SOFTWARE ARCHITECT:
- How does this change affect the rest of the website?
- Does it fit the existing visual style and structure?
- Is the solution maintainable?

Think like a USER (visitor on mobile or desktop):
- Is the page fast to load?
- Is the content clear and easy to read?
- Does it look good on mobile (responsive)?
- Are CTAs visible and compelling?

## Coding rules

- Semantic HTML5
- Mobile-first responsive design
- Keep CSS organized and consistent with existing styles
- Minimize JavaScript, keep it simple
- Optimize images (WebP preferred)
- Slovenian as primary language, English in /en/
- Preserve existing SEO meta tags
- Test that existing pages still work after changes

## Documentation — ALWAYS update

When making changes, ALWAYS update related documentation:
- ai/context.md — if project structure changes
- .cursorrules — if project conventions change

This is mandatory, not optional.

## Changelog — ALWAYS log changes

After completing any code changes, ALWAYS append a summary to ai/changelog.md.

Format:

```
## YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM (Cursor)

**Task:** short description of what was done

**Spremenjene datoteke:** file1.html, file2.css

---
```

This applies to ALL changes — features, fixes, refactors.
